winter mfa documentary film screening winter mfa documentary film screening facebook twitter email print add to calendar four short videos screening of four short videos created by first year students in the mfa program in documentary film and video q&a with filmmakers and reception to follow films to be screened living tiny by paul donatelli and paul meyers a new vision of home is explored in this look at homeowners and builders who seek an alternative to traditional construction neve & sons by duygu erucman and laura green a four generation family business adapts to a globalizing market love & allegiance by tijana petrovic and adam j smith set in a las vegas chapel this film looks at the way in which military service affects romantic relationships tears of men by anna moot levin and sara mott tears of men explores the stigma of men crying through the stories of a few men who hope to reconnect with their tears when wednesday march 16 2011 7 30 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where annenberg auditorium map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students tags film other arts sponsor department of art & art history contact 650 723 3404 risip stanford edu admission free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 270 27049 more info last modified march 14 2011
